nodes.title: Get Width and Height
widgets_values:
from dataclasses import dataclass

class ImageResize:

    @dataclass
    class AspectRatio:
        width: int
        height: int
        name: str
        
        @property
        def ratio(self) -> float:
            return max(self.width / self.height, self.height / self.width)
        
        @property
        def is_landscape(self) -> bool:
            return self.width >= self.height
        
    STANDARD_RATIOS = [
        AspectRatio(512, 512, "1:1"),
        AspectRatio(608, 384, "8:5"),
        AspectRatio(576, 448, "4:3"),
        AspectRatio(608, 416, "3:2"),
        AspectRatio(588, 420, "7:5"),
        AspectRatio(672, 384, "16:9"),
        AspectRatio(768, 320, "21:9"),
        AspectRatio(736, 352, "19:9"),
        AspectRatio(448, 576, "3:4"),
        AspectRatio(416, 608, "2:3"),
        AspectRatio(420, 588, "5:7"),
        AspectRatio(384, 672, "9:16"),
        AspectRatio(320, 768, "9:21"),
        AspectRatio(384, 608, "5:8"),
        AspectRatio(352, 736, "9:19")
    ]
    
    DEFAULT_RATIO = AspectRatio(512, 512, "1:1")
    
    @classmethod
    def standardize(cls, width: int, height: int) -> tuple[int, int]:

        if width <= 0 or height <= 0:
            return cls.DEFAULT_RATIO.width, cls.DEFAULT_RATIO.height

        is_landscape = width >= height
        input_ratio = width / height if is_landscape else height / width
        

        closest_ratio = min(cls.STANDARD_RATIOS, key=lambda r: abs(r.ratio - input_ratio))
        

        if is_landscape != closest_ratio.is_landscape:
            return closest_ratio.height, closest_ratio.width
        
        return closest_ratio.width, closest_ratio.height


_, height, width, _ = image.shape
new_width, new_height = ImageResize.standardize(width, height)
print(new_width, new_height)
